urlLink The Drug War Goes Up in Smoke : "                 The Drug War Goes Up in Smoke                   by Sasha Abramsky  The war on terror may be too new to declare victory or defeat. But the United States has been fighting a declared war on drugs for more than a quarter-century, ever since New York Governor Nelson Rockefeller mandated draconian drug sentencing in 1973--and it's time to announce that this is one war we've lost.